<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39056"><B><FONT SIZE="1" face="Verdana"> My Profile</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucaladel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caladel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/22/01 7:32:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13551.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We sure have come a long long way!</span><hr size=1> /agree were doing well now. If they would just fix up a few holes in our spells(thunder of karana, penalties on paladin only healing spells, breath of tunare ratio), and fix our lvl 55 disc so it works with combat fury or change it entirely....then i  wouldnt really have any more complaints.<br>
<br>
Our damage output is where it should be now, our tanking ability is fine, our survivability is higher then any class; you have to kill us 3+(loh+cc heals) times to kill us, we lack a defining raid ability; but then again so do other classes. With the new group heal we can keep a group alive to aoeing npcs(i could do it before with woh and cc, but its easier now). Just need to fix a few bugs and ill be a happy camper(star control 2 rip off <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
A lot of the AA skills are giving us skills we should have had a long time ago, all the things that make sence. CH loh, 2h bash, holy steed, slay undead. <br>
<br>
The only AA skill i have a gripe with is act of valor, its so grosely underpowered its dead last on my list of skills to get. Then again i dont know if i want it to be too powerful; i dont have a problem with sacraficing my life for others(hell i was always the last member out of a zone when we usto pull a train, way back when 3 years ago), but i dont want the ability to the point of paladins being expected to kill themselves every fight(IE if it was an AOE CH, tho almost nothing short of a group CH would make me spend points on this skill).<br>
<br>
But.... then again i guess it would be fitting, you either keep your group alive with yoru mana, or you sacrafice yourself to keep them alive. ....If you think about it, the noble idea of sacraficing yourself for the sake of others(act of valor) is so soured by the thougt of doing it 20 or 30 times a week that it really isnt noble anymore, its more like dumb for lack of a better word. Think i would be happier if it put us at very low life, and as such it would take tactics to stay live once you use it(or an npc would lock on yoru and smack you down).  IE, you pop CC, then have a bard syncing group da as you lay down act of valor to CH your group; everyone else could click it off, you coudl back out of the fight while DA is active and heal up, then rejoin the fray.<br>
<br>
I digress....overall were doing well these days, and im pretty pleased. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udemottthecavalier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Demott the Cavalier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/22/01 7:53:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13551.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We sure have come a long long way!</span><hr size=1> I am happy with the paladin class, i cant camplain, we defently got out power back and actully balanced(if there is a balance), and we are defenltly a awsome dueling class, and now we are beyond awsome in duels with every bone they toss us.<br>
