<img src=http://www.decordova.com/demott.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urekcim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rekcim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/22/01 9:13:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13551.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We sure have come a long long way!</span><hr size=1> It is amazing the changes that we have gotten over the last 1-2 years.<br>
<br>
The exp penalty removal, casting time on spells counting while swinging, self haste, huge undead procs, 255 defense, 2h improvements, mana pool of parent class, upgrade to melee damage table, good heal spells(56+), many more.<br>
<br>
The class now is almost like a diff. class then it was when I started my pally almost 3 years ago.  Before RoK we were a fantastic class, why would anyone play a warrior or rogue <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  RoK of course anwsered that question and the new question was, Why would anyone play a paladin.  <br>
<br>
Still after all these changes, we still lack a bit.  Granted we are good and useful class, but if EQ taught us anything, its Do something the BEST or get outta the way.  I just get sick of warriors getting these HUGE heads cause they are main assist.  The boss people around and get these god complexes, even though most suck.  To totally balance paladins we need one thing, DEFENSIVE DISCS!!!!   If not we will be second rate everything and always a filler class when another pure class isn't available. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://home.insight.rr.com/cylria/Cyl.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/23/01 12:54:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13551.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: We sure have come a long long way!</span><hr size=1> I hate to be the downer &lt;again&gt;, but I should clarify something Reckim.<br>
<br>
The mana pool of the parent class was actually a cleverly disguised nerf. What VI didn't annouce right away was that they increased the mana cost of all spells for hybrids. Basically we have more mana, but we still can cast the same spell about the same number of times as before. The difference now is that it takes us longer to recover mana.<br>
